{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Rubber Research Institute of Malaysia |nativename_a = Institut Penyelidikan Getah Malaysia |nativename_r = |logo = Rubber Research Institute of Malaya (R.R.I.M), Jalan Ampang.jpg |logo_width = 250px |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 29 June 1925 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Malaysia]] |headquarters = [[Ampang, Kuala Lumpur|Ampang]], [[Kuala Lumpur]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = [[Malaysian Rubber Board]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = |footnotes = }}
The '''Rubber Research Institute of Malaysia''' ('''RRIM'''; {{lang-ms|Institut Penyelidikan Getah Malaysia}}) is a research center for problems and matters pertaining to rubber and its industry in [[Malaysia]].
==History== On 29 June 1925, the bill to incorporate the '''Rubber Research Institute of Malaya''' was passed by the government. Dr G. Bryce was appointed the first Director of the institute on 26 September 1926. On 31 October 1926, its laboratory at Petaling Estate was closed down and from 1 November 1926, the institute took over the equipment of the Rubber Growers' Association. Also in 1926, the institute made a request to the government for the temporary laboratory building of the institute at [[Jalan Damansara|Damansara Road]] in [[Selangor]]. The request was granted and the building was leased for five years. In 1936, the institute decided to relocate to a new building at [[Jalan Ampang|Ampang Road]]. The building was officiated by [[Sultan of Selangor|Selangor Sultan]] [[Sulaiman of Selangor|Sulaiman]] on 22 April 1936 and the institute restarted its operation on 19 May 1937.<ref name="lgm">{{cite web|url=http://www.lgm.gov.my/general/rrim70yrs.aspx|publisher=lgm.gov.my|title=General Information - The Origin and Establishment of RRIM|accessdate=2016-11-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.insulflex.com.my/about_us/certificates/certificate_231110/Rubber_Research_Institute_ASTMD1171_(Ozone_Test).pdf|date=27 April 1995|title=Test Report|website=Insulflex|publisher=Rubber Research Institute of Malaysia|accessdate=9 November 2016}}</ref>
